-- Ecopetrol, Light, Vale, Banco de Credito del Peru : Latin Equity Preview
-- Eduardo Thomson
-- 2010-06-14T09:23:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/ecopetrol-light-vale-banco-de-credito-del-peru-latin-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  gained 1.2 percent to 3,805.63.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Brazil  
 Light SA  (LIGT3 BS): The power distributor said it acquired
a 51 percent stake in Axxiom Solucoes Tecnologicas SA, a company
that provides information technology services to power, gas and
water utilities sectors. Light rose 0.8 percent to 21.10 reais.  
 Vale SA  (VALE5 BS): Chief Executive Officer Roger Agnelli
said June 11 to reporters that cutting import steel taxes could
hurt competition and bring “serious consequences.” Brazil’s
government is considering a cut on steel duties to contain
inflation after wholesale prices rose the most in two years.
Vale rose 1.1 percent to 41.66 reais.  
 Colombia  
 Ecopetrol SA  (ECOPETL CB): The board of Colombia’s state-
controlled oil company approved a request to extend the
commercially operative surface at the Rubiales oil field by more
than 7,000 hectares, a plan that could increase production at
the field to 170,000 barrels of oil per day by 2011, from
122,500 barrels per day. Ecopetrol closed unchanged at 2,710
pesos.  
 Peru  
 Banco de Credito del Peru  (CREDITC1 PE): The Peruvian bank
and the Bank of Nova Scotia’s Peruvian unit said they will lend
liquefied natural gas exporter Peru LNG $75 million to fund
“short term needs”, Banco de Credito said in a filing. Its
stock rose 1.4 percent to 7.3 soles.  
